description: View from Pen-y-Crug summit towards Pen-y-Fan and Corn Du. Pen-y-Crug is a hill on the northern edge of Bannau Brycheiniog National Park, just north of the town of Brecon/Aberhonddu. Several gorse bushes can be seen in the foreground.

author: Dominic Nelson
attribution_text: Dominic Nelson (CC BY-SA 4.0) via Wikimedia Commons
description: The villages of Cradoc and Battle as seen from the summit of Pen-y-Crug, an Iron Age hillfort in Powys, Wales. Some gorse bushes can be seen in the foreground.

Seen from the grounds of Llanthony Priory, looking north towards Gospel Pass.
